# Next.js Best Practices & Rules

## Tech Stack Prefereces
- Framework: Next.js 14+ (App Router)
- Language: TypeScript (Strict mode)
- Styling: Tailwind CSS
- Components: Lucide React for icons, Shadcn UI for components
- State Management: React Context or Zustand (if needed)

## Coding Standards
- Use 'use client' directive only when necessary (Interactivity, Browser APIs, Hooks).
- Favor Server Components for data fetching.
- Use Async/Await for data fetching in Server Components.
- Functional Components: Use Arrow Functions (`const Component = () => ...`).
- File Naming: Use lowercase with dashes (kebab-case) for routing folders.

## Best Practices
- Image Optimization: Always use `next/image`.
- Routing: Use the `Link` component from `next/link` for internal navigation.
- SEO: Use the Metadata API (generateMetadata) instead of the <Head> tag.
- Error Handling: Always implement `error.tsx` and `loading.tsx` for route segments.

## Windsurf Specific Flow
- Before creating a new component, check if a similar one exists in `@/components/ui`.
- When fixing bugs, always check the Terminal output and browser console logs.
- After installing new packages, run `npm run dev` to ensure no dependency conflicts.